    "summary": "Expertise in: intercultural communication, cultural analysis, ethnography, local food systems, sustainable development, social and community development, and case management.\n\nVersatile, open-minded, and adventurous social professional with a strong connection to the Middle East. Since 2020 Tripoli is my second home and I am happily dividing my time and presence between the Netherlands and Lebanon while working on several projects. \n\nMy background serves as a guideline for impact; through my experiences, I understand what impact looks like and what it means in practice. I combine sensitivity, open-mindedness, and curiosity, with a practical and analytical approach. I'm an advocate of applied anthropology, convinced of the usefulness of bringing deep cultural knowledge to any setting and grasping the complexity of everyday life in the bigger picture.  As a networker and an intercultural communicator, I search to connect people with each other and facilitate in-depth understanding. I go, see and experience first-hand, to develop myself as a well-advised professional with sensitivity to different contexts:\n\nIn the combination of this all, I am good at (cultural) assessments and analysis; critical thinking; strategizing projects; monitoring development, and telling stories that illuminate the meaning in the bigger picture. Both in my impact-driven approach and my development as a writer, I search to connect abstract theories and concepts to the fascinating everyday life practice. I believe this is where the magic happens.",
